Abhishek Pachlaniya : Right quote for binary search in c++.
mark42 : Here's a simple implementation of binary search in C++:
```cpp
int binarySearch(int array[], int n, int target) {
    int left = 0;
    int right = n - 1;
    while (left <= right) {
        int mid = left + (right - left) / 2;
        if (array[mid] == target) {
            return mid;
        } else if (array[mid] < target) {
            left = mid + 1;
        } else {
            right = mid - 1;
        }
    }
    return -1;
}
```
This function takes a sorted array, its size `n`, and a target value as input. It returns the index of the target value if it's found in the array; otherwise, it returns -1.
